				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Is there an intrinsic way in hardware? No. Tokumaru's suggestion is it.<br /><br />If you always update the shadow copy of the bank number <em>before</em> you change it, it can't get out of sync due to NMI or IRQ interruption. The same method works safely for MMC3 $8000.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

