				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If an interrupt needs to change banks, such as the NMI handler having to map in the sound engine/data bank, just read the current bank's number from ROM and push it to the stack before bankswitching, and when you're done, pull it from the stack and map that bank back in. This should work even if multiple interrupts that need to switch banks occur on top of each other.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

